: "NONE", "body_html": "<p>I find that the model file size is three times bigger after I switch optimizer from <code>tf.train.GradientDescentOptimizer</code> to <code>tf.train.AdamOptimizer</code>. And here is the reason I found on stackoverflow:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>ADAM adds two running means (for gradient and square of gradient) as additional non-trainable parameters for each trainable parameter</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Thus, is there any way to reduce the model fie size of adam optimizer?</p>\n<p>THANKS!!</p>", "body_text": "I find that the model file size is three times bigger after I switch optimizer from tf.train.GradientDescentOptimizer to tf.train.AdamOptimizer. And here is the reason I found on stackoverflow:\n\nADAM adds two running means (for gradient and square of gradient) as additional non-trainable parameters for each trainable parameter\n\nThus, is there any way to reduce the model fie size of adam optimizer?\nTHANKS!!", "body": "I find that the model file size is three times bigger after I switch optimizer from `tf.train.GradientDescentOptimizer` to `tf.train.AdamOptimizer`. And here is the reason I found on stackoverflow:\r\n\r\n>ADAM adds two running means (for gradient and square of gradient) as additional non-trainable parameters for each trainable parameter\r\n\r\nThus, is there any way to reduce the model fie size of adam optimizer?\r\n\r\nTHANKS!!"}